    &lt;Title&gt;Absolutely appauled&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;My father has recently been diagnosed with prostate cancer, we were told that chemotherapy was the best option. 

Anyhow we were asked to attend an app at Ward 16 last week, Only to be told that we don’t have an appointment and whoever spoke to us had not put that on the system. We were then told to wait to see if their was anything they could do, to get us seen. We waited for an hour just to be told our chemo had expired 3 hours prior our “appointment”. So not only were we not booked we had an expired treatment.  Anyhow we were re booked for the following day at 2pm. We were waiting in one waiting room then put in another waiting room, it was musical chairs at its best. The icing on the cake was our treatment did not start till 6:00 and we did not leave the ward till 8.  Their was over 30 patients and one nurse was running the show. How is that even acceptable considering the sensitivity and vunerabilty of these patients. The cherry on top of the cake was when we were told we can ring the ward 24/7 for any concerns or if my father feels unwell, only when we tried nobody and I mean nobody answered. We’re considereing going private.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
